---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use | ZoningBase"
  description="ZoningBase terms of use. Conditions for using the US zoning code database."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-text-muted text-sm">Last updated: April 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          By accessing and using ZoningBase ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Nature of the Service</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          ZoningBase provides structured zoning code data sourced from publicly available municipal records. The Service is a reference tool designed for informational purposes only.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Zoning ordinances are subject to change. While we make reasonable efforts to maintain accurate and current data, ZoningBase does not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of any information on the Service. Data may not reflect recent amendments, variances, or rezoning actions.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong>ZoningBase is not a substitute for professional legal, planning, or real estate advice.</strong> Always verify zoning data with the relevant municipal planning department before making development, investment, or land use decisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          ZoningBase and its operators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or inability to use, the Service or any information provided through the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The structure, design, and presentation of data on ZoningBase is proprietary. The underlying zoning code data is sourced from public records. You may reference ZoningBase data for personal or professional use but may not scrape, reproduce, or redistribute the database in bulk without written permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms of Use at any time. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 font-medium text-sm">
        &larr; Back to all states
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
